{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":829,"text":"I teach chemistry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3048,"text":"(Explosion)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":4414,"text":"All right, all right."},{"time":7572,"text":"So more than just explosions,"},{"time":9853,"text":"chemistry is everywhere."},{"time":11464,"text":"Have you ever found yourself at a restaurant spacing out"},{"time":14104,"text":"just doing this over and over?"},{"time":16449,"text":"Some people nodding yes."},{"time":18654,"text":"Recently, I showed this to my students,"},{"time":20982,"text":"and I just asked them to try and explain why it happened."},{"time":25331,"text":"The questions and conversations that followed"},{"time":27952,"text":"were fascinating."},{"time":29603,"text":"Check out this video that Maddie"},{"time":31417,"text":"from my period three class sent me that evening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45104,"text":"(Clang) (Laughs)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":47569,"text":"Now obviously, as Maddie's chemistry teacher,"},{"time":50763,"text":"I love that she went home and continued to geek out"},{"time":53869,"text":"about this kind of ridiculous demonstration"},{"time":56487,"text":"that we did in class."},{"time":57909,"text":"But what fascinated me more is that Maddie's curiosity"},{"time":60855,"text":"took her to a new level."},{"time":62549,"text":"If you look inside that beaker,"},{"time":64682,"text":"you might see a candle."},{"time":66242,"text":"Maddie's using temperature to extend this phenomenon"},{"time":69251,"text":"to a new scenario."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72028,"text":"You know, questions and curiosity like Maddie's"},{"time":75266,"text":"are magnets that draw us towards our teachers,"},{"time":78232,"text":"and they transcend all technology"},{"time":81184,"text":"or buzzwords in education."},{"time":84325,"text":"But if we place these technologies before student inquiry,"},{"time":88426,"text":"we can be robbing ourselves"},{"time":90549,"text":"of our greatest tool as teachers: our students' questions."},{"time":95483,"text":"For example, flipping a boring lecture from the classroom"},{"time":99863,"text":"to the screen of a mobile device"},{"time":101640,"text":"might save instructional time,"},{"time":103477,"text":"but if it is the focus of our students' experience,"},{"time":106376,"text":"it's the same dehumanizing chatter"},{"time":109496,"text":"just wrapped up in fancy clothing."},{"time":111728,"text":"But if instead we have the guts"},{"time":114003,"text":"to confuse our students, perplex them,"},{"time":116873,"text":"and evoke real questions,"},{"time":119149,"text":"through those questions, we as teachers have information"},{"time":122149,"text":"that we can use to tailor robust"},{"time":125177,"text":"and informed methods of blended instruction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128868,"text":"So, 21st-century lingo jargon mumbo jumbo aside,"},{"time":134040,"text":"the truth is, I've been teaching for 13 years now,"},{"time":138244,"text":"and it took a life-threatening situation"},{"time":140718,"text":"to snap me out of 10 years of pseudo-teaching"},{"time":143665,"text":"and help me realize that student questions"},{"time":147280,"text":"are the seeds of real learning,"},{"time":150401,"text":"not some scripted curriculum"},{"time":152515,"text":"that gave them tidbits of random information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155811,"text":"In May of 2010, at 35 years old,"},{"time":159283,"text":"with a two-year-old at home and my second child on the way,"},{"time":162376,"text":"I was diagnosed with a large aneurysm"},{"time":164992,"text":"at the base of my thoracic aorta."},{"time":167512,"text":"This led to open-heart surgery. This is the actual real email"},{"time":170564,"text":"from my doctor right there."},{"time":172098,"text":"Now, when I got this, I was -- press Caps Lock --"},{"time":175623,"text":"absolutely freaked out, okay?"},{"time":178088,"text":"But I found surprising moments of comfort"},{"time":182307,"text":"in the confidence that my surgeon embodied."},{"time":185997,"text":"Where did this guy get this confidence, the audacity of it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":189441,"text":"So when I asked him, he told me three things."},{"time":193033,"text":"He said first, his curiosity drove him"},{"time":196415,"text":"to ask hard questions about the procedure,"},{"time":198690,"text":"about what worked and what didn't work."},{"time":201875,"text":"Second, he embraced, and didn't fear,"},{"time":204969,"text":"the messy process of trial and error,"},{"time":207045,"text":"the inevitable process of trial and error."},{"time":209554,"text":"And third, through intense reflection,"},{"time":212530,"text":"he gathered the information that he needed"},{"time":215206,"text":"to design and revise the procedure,"},{"time":217112,"text":"and then, with a steady hand, he saved my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220633,"text":"Now I absorbed a lot from these words of wisdom,"},{"time":224309,"text":"and before I went back into the classroom that fall,"},{"time":226289,"text":"I wrote down three rules of my own"},{"time":229547,"text":"that I bring to my lesson planning still today."},{"time":232327,"text":"Rule number one: Curiosity comes first."},{"time":236369,"text":"Questions can be windows to great instruction,"},{"time":239468,"text":"but not the other way around."},{"time":242158,"text":"Rule number two: Embrace the mess."},{"time":245792,"text":"We're all teachers. We know learning is ugly."},{"time":248463,"text":"And just because the scientific method is allocated"},{"time":251334,"text":"to page five of section 1.2 of chapter one"},{"time":254785,"text":"of the one that we all skip, okay,"},{"time":258240,"text":"trial and error can still be an informal part"},{"time":261442,"text":"of what we do every single day"},{"time":263359,"text":"at Sacred Heart Cathedral in room 206."},{"time":266691,"text":"And rule number three: Practice reflection."},{"time":270713,"text":"What we do is important. It deserves our care,"},{"time":273057,"text":"but it also deserves our revision."},{"time":276289,"text":"Can we be the surgeons of our classrooms?"},{"time":279067,"text":"As if what we are doing one day will save lives."},{"time":282063,"text":"Our students our worth it."},{"time":283614,"text":"And each case is different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286049,"text":"(Explosion)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":287144,"text":"All right. Sorry."},{"time":289091,"text":"The chemistry teacher in me just needed to get that"},{"time":290999,"text":"out of my system before we move on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293834,"text":"So these are my daughters."},{"time":295619,"text":"On the right we have little Emmalou -- Southern family."},{"time":299291,"text":"And, on the left, Riley."},{"time":302073,"text":"Now Riley's going to be a big girl in a couple weeks here."},{"time":304728,"text":"She's going to be four years old,"},{"time":306422,"text":"and anyone who knows a four-year-old"},{"time":308672,"text":"knows that they love to ask, \"Why?\""},{"time":311872,"text":"Yeah. Why."},{"time":313356,"text":"I could teach this kid anything"},{"time":315666,"text":"because she is curious about everything."},{"time":318516,"text":"We all were at that age."},{"time":320999,"text":"But the challenge is really for Riley's future teachers,"},{"time":324474,"text":"the ones she has yet to meet."},{"time":327296,"text":"How will they grow this curiosity?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":329788,"text":"You see, I would argue that Riley is a metaphor for all kids,"},{"time":335270,"text":"and I think dropping out of school comes in many different forms --"},{"time":338664,"text":"to the senior who's checked out before the year's even begun"},{"time":341988,"text":"or that empty desk in the back of an urban middle school's classroom."},{"time":347006,"text":"But if we as educators leave behind"},{"time":349681,"text":"this simple role as disseminators of content"},{"time":352263,"text":"and embrace a new paradigm"},{"time":354600,"text":"as cultivators of curiosity and inquiry,"},{"time":357644,"text":"we just might bring a little bit more meaning"},{"time":359869,"text":"to their school day, and spark their imagination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362584,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364168,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}